tool.name: temporalVisuals

param.name: targetsFC
param.dialogReference: Input dark targets feature class produced by the "3_Temporal Persistence Analysis" tool. This feature class can either be the consolidated result for a specific year (for example, "RS2_2010"), or the overall multi-year analysis result ("persistent_targets").

param.name: persisRadius
param.dialogReference:
These values are the distances with which the visualizations will be produced. Any number of distance values may be selected, which are measured in meters.

Distance values available here are those that have already been analyzed and calculated by the "3_Temporal Persistence Analysis" script tool.

tool.summary:
This tool displays the results of the "3_Temporal Persistence Analysis" script tool visually in a map document. The desired radius distance is selected and the analysis results are displayed as a group layer consisting of a persistence count, weight value and cluster groups, along with a layer of filered dark targets and a layer with all unfiltered dark targets.The results are produced and saved in the "Results" folder entitled "analysis_results.mxd".

The layer of unfiltered dark targets contains hyperlinks for each polygon which loads the 8 bit raster RADARSAT-2 image from which the original dark target was extracted. This allows for quick reference to the relevant RADARSAT-2 image.These links rely on a relative path to find the corresponding images in the "Products" directory. In order for these links to work, the "analysis_results.mxd" must be kept and accessed in the "Results" folder.

A heat map indicating concentrations of filtered dark targets is also produced.
